---
check_id: BC
name: "New Tests + Regression"
applies_to: all
---
[BC] NEW TESTS + REGRESSION — zero new failures allowed

STEP 1: Run only the test file created in Step 1.
  Required: all pass.

  DIAGNOSE FIRST — before fixing anything:
    Run the test with verbose output (e.g., --verbose, -v, or equivalent).
    Check for these common test faults:
      - Hardcoded values: assertion uses a literal number/string instead of a computed value
      - Empty mocks: mock returns undefined/null/empty array for every call
      - Wrong target: test asserts on a different method/class than the acceptance criterion
      - Missing setup: test doesn't initialize required dependencies or fixtures
      - Flaky timing: test depends on setTimeout, Promise, or async without awaiting

    If ANY test fault is found:
      Print: "TEST FAULT DETECTED — [fault type]: [details]"
      Fix the TEST, not the implementation.
      Re-run step 1.

    If NO test fault is found:
      Print: "Test fault check passed — fault is in implementation."
      Proceed to fix the implementation.

  If any fail: fix the implementation. Do not weaken the tests to make them pass.

  FLAKY TEST PROTOCOL: follow guides/flaky-test-protocol.md.
    Additional requirement: if a test passes on the first run but you
    suspect timing- or state-dependency, run it 5 times consecutively
    ([test runner command] --repeat=5). If it fails on any run, treat
    as flaky. Fix the root cause before marking DONE.

STEP 2: Run the full test suite (all tests, not just the new ones):
  For all task types except frontend-feature and e2e:
    plan.md §13 regression_command.api_only
  For frontend-feature and e2e tasks:
    plan.md §13 regression_command.all
  Required: ZERO new test failures.
  If a previously passing test now fails:
    This task introduced a regression. Do not mark DONE.
    Identify exactly which change broke the existing test.
    Fix the regression, then re-run the full regression suite.
    Print: "REGRESSION FOUND AND FIXED — [test name]: [root cause and fix]"

  If the regression cannot be fixed (conflicting requirements, unresolvable
  architecture clash):
    1. Mark the task ABANDONED in tasks.md with a note explaining the clash.
    2. Print: "REGRESSION UNFIXABLE — ABANDONING task. See rollback note."
    3. Do NOT mark the task DONE.
    4. Do NOT weaken existing tests to make them pass.

Print: "NEW+REGRESSION: [N] new tests pass, [total N] total tests, 0 new failures"
